  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Boss
    The Boss class represents the final enemy which the Hero can defeat with all of the same abilities as the Hero.
    Checkpoint
    The Checkpoint class represents a checkpoint which the hero can activate to respawn to.
    Circle
    The Circle class represents a double precision Circle.
    DrawingSurface
    The DrawingSurface class represents the surface on which the Active Screen is drawn.
    Enemy
    The Enemy class represents an enemy which can move and deal damage to the Hero.
    Fireball
    The Fireball class represents a fire ball which is a projectile that can be thrown.
    FireEnemy
    The FireEnemy class represents an Enemy with the Fireball projectile which the Player can defeat.
    FirstScreen
    The FirstScreen class represents an Option Menu.
    GameScreen
    The GameScreen represents the game screen and has all of the Enemies, Platforms, Checkpoints, Spikes and Hero.
    GrassEnemy
    The GrassEnemy class represents an Enemy with the Leaf Dash move which the Player can defeat.
    Heart
    The Heart class represents a heart which the Hero can collect to gain health
    Hero
    The Hero class represents the playable main character which can move and use special abilities.
    InstructionScreen
    The InstructionScreen class represents the Screen which displays the instructions and the keyboard layout.
    Main
    Main class that runs the program and has the drawing surface and window.
    MovingImage
    The MovingImage class represents an image which can move.
    MovingPlatform
    The MovingPlatform class represents a movable platform which the Hero can interact with.
    MusicPlayer
    The MusicPlayer class represents a music player which can play, pause, and loop clips.
    Screen
    The abstract class Screen represents a Screen Outside Code Credit: ProcessingScreenSwitchingDemo
    Spike
    The Spike class represents a Spike which can cause damage to the Hero if they walk into it.
    Token
    A token object which the hero can collect
    VictoryScreen
    The VictoryScreen represents the victory screen drawn when the Boss is defeated.
    WaterEnemy
    The WaterEnemy class represents an Enemy which can create a Waterfall which the Player can defeat.
    WaterWave
    The Waterwave class represents a water wave that extends outward dealing damage.
